 Sept. 15: Exxon suspends its beach cleanup for the winter, claiming it has left 1,100 miles of oiled beaches ``environmentally stable'' and saying its 25-week cleanup involving more than 10,000 workers was a job well done.
 Jan. 22: Hazelwood goes on trial in Anchorage, facing charges of criminal mischief, reckless endangerment, negligent discharge of oil, and operating a vessel while intoxicated.
